AddConfigurationPanel $Id: package-summary.html,v 1.10 2009/08/14 21:13:33 tizatt Exp $ JPanel that allows the user to add a new Configuration Object to the program.
AddJobPanel JPanel that allows the user to add a Job by specifying the Query ID and the Configuration ID.
AddQueryPanel JPanel that consists of With seven JLabels and seven JTextFields that allow the user to input all the query information.
ExecutePanel $Id: package-summary.html,v 1.10 2009/08/14 21:13:33 tizatt Exp $ Creates a panel with two JButtons: one that allow the user to perform all the jobs that have been inputed, and another that allows the user to write all of the inputed queries, configurations, and jobs, to an XML file
SolPickerFrame The program SolPicker retrieves a sequence specified by the user from a web server, creates oligos, and filters those oligos based on a set of parameters, returning a list of valid and discarded oligos.
